   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health for 45 indigenous communities in Mexico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our foundation has been working with indigenous communities in Mexico for 42 years,helping to generate local development and to improve living conditions.The most impoverished communities in Chiapas are suffering the increasing difficulty of access to health services,because of this we intend to promote a project to generate alternative health services in the area to cover the health needs of 45 indigenous communities covering 15000 people and thereby decreasing the % mortality and malnutrition.</narrative>
